HEADWORD: Eudoxian
<hw>Eu*dox"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of Eudoxius, patriarch of Antioch and
Constantinople in the 4th century, and a celebrated defender of the
doctrines of Arius.</def>⟦br⟧
